ASSIGNMENT, CO-TENANCY, AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT This ASSIGNMENT, CO-TENANCY, AND SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (the “Agreement”) is made and entered into as of July 23, 2020 (the “Effective Date”) by and among Crowned Ridge Wind, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Crowned Ridge 1”), Crowned Ridge Wind II, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“Crowned Ridge 2”), and each Person from time to time that becomes a party hereto (each sometimes referred to herein individually as a “Party” and collectively as the “Parties”). Each of Crowned Ridge 1, Crowned Ridge 2 and each new Owner pursuant to this Agreement is sometimes referred to herein individually as an “Owner” and collectively the “Owners.” RECITALS A. Crowned Ridge 1 constructed a wind power generation facility in Codington, Deuel, and Grant Counties, South Dakota, with a Nameplate Capacity of 200.1 MW (the “Crowned Ridge 1 Project”). B. Crowned Ridge 2 is constructing a wind power generation facility in Codington, Deuel, and Grant Counties, South Dakota, adjacent to and to the south of the Crowned Ridge 1 Project, with a Nameplate Capacity of 200.6 MW (the “Crowned Ridge 2 Project”). C. In connection with the Crowned Ridge 1 Project, Crowned Ridge 1 caused to be constructed a 230kV generator tie-line interconnected into transmission facilities owned by Otter Tail Power Company (“Otter Tail”) and within the MISO transmission system, as depicted on Exhibit A (the “Transmission Line”). D. Crowned Ridge Interconnection, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (“CR Interconnection”), is party to a generator interconnection agreement with MISO and Otter Tail (the “Interconnection Agreement”) with respect to the Crowned Ridge 1 Project and the Crowned Ridge 2 Project, and will utilize the Transmission Line to deliver all of the energy generated by the Projects to the physical point of interconnection with the MISO grid. E. Pursuant to that certain Amended and Restated Purchase and Sale Agreement, dated as of August 16, 2019, by and between ESI Energy, LLC (“PSA Seller”) and Northern States Power Company (“PSA Buyer”), as may be amended from time to time (the “PSA”), ownership of Crowned Ridge 2 will pass from PSA Seller to PSA Buyer at the Closing (as defined in the PSA). E. The Parties are entering into this Agreement to describe their relative ownership interests in, and the Owners’ respective rights and obligations with respect to, the Shared Assets. This Agreement shall be the Owners’ expression of their intention to establish and impose mutually beneficial limitations, restrictions, covenants and conditions to provide for the proper and orderly ownership, operation and management of their respective Projects and the Shared Assets. OWNERSHIP AND USE OF SHARED ASSETS Ownership of Shared Assets; Owners’ Intent. After the Effective Date of this Agreement, and subject to obtaining any necessary approval from FERC under Section 203 of the Federal Power Act, the Parties shall consummate certain transfers and conveyances of interests in the Shared Assets pursuant to the following instruments (the “Transfer Documents”), each of which shall be recorded contemporaneously with, and immediately following, a memorandum or short form of this Agreement in the real estate records of the applicable public registries: An assignment and assumption agreement by and between Crowned Ridge 1 and Crowned Ridge 2 in which (A) Crowned Ridge 1 assigns to Crowned Ridge 2 an undivided ownership interest, as tenants-in-common, in the Shared Agreements and the Shared Real Property Interests; A special warranty deed by Crowned Ridge 1 conveying to Crowned Ridge 2 an undivided ownership interest, as tenants-in-common, in the Shared Infrastructure and the fee simple parcels that are the subject of the Shared Real Property Documents; For purposes of clarification, immediately following the consummation of the transfers contemplated by the Transfer Documents, the Parties intend for each Owner to own an undivided ownership interest in the Shared Assets, as tenants-in-common, subject to and in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement. The Owners acknowledge and agree that aside from services under this Agreement, no Owner will provide any interconnection or transmission services to the other Owners under this Agreement. Use of Shared Assets; Owner Responsibilities. The Parties acknowledge and agree that Otter Tail may require the use of the Shared Assets for the co-location of certain control, metering and monitoring equipment servicing and connecting the Projects to the Transmission Line. The Parties agree to cooperate in good faith to provide Otter Tail with rights to use the Shared Assets to so service the Projects. To the extent any curtailment or disconnection of a Project is directly caused by an act or omission of an Owner of a different Project constituting negligence or willful misconduct or the breach by an Owner of this Agreement, then such Owner shall be solely responsible for any and all lost revenues, costs and/or expenses (including the cash value of any lost federal production tax credits, grossed-up based on the actual combined state and federal income tax rate applicable to such Owner) incurred by the other Owners for any curtailment of some or all of the energy production attributable to such act, omission or breach; provided, however, that in no event shall such Owner be liable for any such lost revenues, costs and/or expenses exceeding $1,000,000 per occurrence. Priority of Use. In the event the Facilities Manager becomes aware of an equipment failure or an unanticipated event that requires the use of the Shared Assets to be curtailed to protect the Shared Assets, any Project, or human life, the Facilities Manager shall immediately notify each Owner or its designated scheduling agent. The Owners agree to cooperate (either directly or through their respective scheduling agents) to curtail their Projects in response to such unanticipated event. During such curtailment each Owner shall curtail a Proportionate Share of its respective Project. To the extent any such curtailment or disconnection is directly caused by one Owner’s Project or the breach by an Owner of this Agreement, then, notwithstanding Section 2.3(a) above, such Owner’s Project shall be the first Project to be curtailed to the extent necessary or disconnected and, subject to the last sentence of this Section 2.3(b), the last Project to be permitted to fully use the Shared Assets following any such curtailment or disconnection. Such Owner whose Project caused another Project to be curtailed shall be solely responsible for any and all lost revenues, costs and/or expenses (including the cash value of any lost federal production tax credits, grossed-up based on the actual combined state and federal income tax rate applicable to such Owner) incurred by the other Owner for any curtailment of some or all of the energy production; provided, however, that in no event shall such Owner be liable for any such lost revenues, costs and/or expenses exceeding $1,000,000 per occurrence. Such Owner’s Project shall not be permitted to use the Shared Assets again unless and until the Facilities Manager determines that the deficiencies have been corrected, or the Owners otherwise agree. New Owners. Subject to the requirements and protections of FERC Order No. 807, (i) no Person may be admitted as a new Owner under this Agreement with the right to use the Shared Assets unless such Person is an Affiliate of Crowned Ridge 1 and has complied with this Section 2.4, Article 8 and the other terms of this Agreement, and (ii) a Person may only be admitted as a new Owner to the extent the Transmission Line Unused Capacity is greater than 0 MW, and such new Owner’s Project does not have a Nameplate Capacity greater than such Transmission Line Unused Capacity. Following the addition of any new Owner, each Owner’s Proportionate Share hereunder shall then be re-calculated by the Facilities Manager to reflect the new Proportionate Shares of the existing Owners and the new Owner. Each new Owner shall be responsible for maintaining such rights as are necessary to interconnect its Project with the transmission provider’s interconnection facilities using the Shared Assets, and to deliver the electrical energy generated by its Project to the transmission provider’s interconnection facilities at its Project’s point of interconnection, as consistent with the terms and conditions of this Agreement and the Interconnection Agreement; provided that the rights and obligations of CR Interconnection, on behalf of the existing Owners, under the Interconnection Agreement are not adversely affected thereby. Each new Owner shall be solely responsible for any and all costs of (i) making any filings for regulatory compliance required by, or participating in any regulatory proceedings that arise out of, the addition of such new Owner, (ii) any fees and expenses payable to amend this Agreement, and the Shared Real Property Documents to provide for the addition of such new Owner, and (iii) including all consultant, expert and attorneys’ costs expenses and fees incurred in connection with the above. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein, any additional facilities, real property rights, operational components, upgrades, modifications, improvements or other option or construction rights to or for the Shared Assets that are constructed or acquired by any Owner, or any Affiliate thereof, shall be: (i) procured by such Owner (and not any Affiliate thereof) for and on behalf of itself and the other Owners, (ii) added as Shared Assets hereunder and deemed incorporated into, and governed by, the terms hereof, and (iii) owned by the Owners in accordance with the terms of this Agreement. At the request of any Owner, the Owners shall execute such documents as are necessary or desirable to document such ownership. Station Service. Each Owner shall be responsible for paying for the retail station power service of its Project. OPERATION AND MAINTENANCE OF SHARED ASSETS; EXPENSES Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Assets. All Paying Owners’ Expenses and other costs of operating and maintaining the Shared Assets in accordance herewith, as well as costs attributable thereto, shall be paid by each Paying Owner to Facilities Manager in accordance with the Paying Owners’ Proportionate Share of each Paying Owner. For the avoidance of doubt, Crowned Ridge 2 shall not have any responsibility or liability for any expenses, costs, fees or other amounts with respect to the Shared Assets. The Facilities Manager, as authorized agent for each Paying Owner, shall administer the collection of Paying Owners’ Expenses through a monthly invoice to each Paying Owner. Each Paying Owner shall pay each such invoice within thirty (30) days after receipt thereof. Removal or Replacement of Owner Property. Each Owner shall have the express right, at any time and in its sole discretion, to remove and/or replace any part of its Project and all other property owned by such Owner, to the extent not jointly owned by the Owners. If removal or replacement of any of such property will materially affect in an adverse way the safety or operation of any of the Shared Assets, the Owner contemplating the removal or replacement shall consult with and obtain the consent of each of the other Owners before conducting the contemplated removal or replacement, such consent not to be unreasonably withheld, conditioned or delayed. Notwithstanding the foregoing, in no event shall any Owner alter any existing improvements located on the real property described in the Shared Real Property Documents, nor install, erect or construct new such improvements thereon, without the approval of the Owners’ Committee (other than in such Owner’s capacity as Facilities Manager as expressly provided in this Agreement). FACILITIES MANAGEMENT Facilities Manager. Crowned Ridge 1 shall be the initial “Facilities Manager” subject to its right to resign as Facilities Manager upon one hundred eighty (180) calendar days’ notice to the Owners. If Crowned Ridge 1 (or any other entity) resigns as Facilities Manager, the successor Facilities Manager shall be selected by the outgoing Facilities Manager or the Owners’ Committee, in accordance with Sections 4.1(b) or 4.1(c), as applicable. The initial Facilities Manager shall serve for a term of twenty (20) years. Subject to Section 4.1(c), no later than one hundred eighty (180) calendar days prior to the end of such term, the outgoing Facilities Manager shall choose its successor and the period of time for the next succeeding term. If the Facilities Manager is a third party, such party shall provide services pursuant to a contract satisfactory to the Owners’ Committee and consistent with (but not limited to) the requirements that would be applicable to the Facilities Manager pursuant to this Agreement if the Facilities Manager were one of the Owners. The foregoing shall apply with respect to each successive term until this Agreement is terminated. If the Facilities Manager is removed pursuant to Section 4.4 or Section 9.4(b), the Owners’ Committee shall appoint the next Facilities Manager (such successor, however, may not be the Owner that has been acting as the removed Facilities Manager), and choose the period of time for the next succeeding term. Powers and Duties of Facilities Manager. The Facilities Manager shall be authorized and obligated to do the following on behalf of each of the Owners; provided, however, that the Facilities Manager shall not be bound by a fiduciary duty to the Owners: Operate and maintain the Shared Assets in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice, applicable Laws, the Shared Real Property Documents, and the Interconnection Agreement, and commercially reasonable terms included in any insurance policies covering the Shared Assets of which the Facilities Manager has received notice. The Facilities Manager either directly or through one or more subcontractors will provide for the operations and maintenance of the Shared Assets, including procurement of spare parts and such other services as may be reasonably necessary consistent with Prudent Industry Practice and applicable Laws. In connection with any scheduled operation and maintenance, upon reasonable notice to the Owner(s) affected, the Facilities Manager is authorized to require each Owner, upon no less than five (5) Business Days’ notice, to disconnect all or any portions of its Project, in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice and in compliance with the terms of this Agreement. The Facilities Manager shall coordinate with the Owner(s) affected to schedule the interruption, to the extent possible consistent with the standards set forth above, at a time least likely to adversely affect such Owners’ Projects, and to minimize the length of the interruption. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, and subject to Section 2.3, the Facilities Manager shall operate and maintain the Shared Assets in a non-discriminatory manner, treating each Owner and its Project equally and fairly. Maintain books and records related to the Shared Assets in accordance with generally acceptable accounting principles and international financial reporting standards (as adopted by the International Accounting Standards Board from time to time) applicable to the electric utility industry; Procure policies of insurance in accordance with Section 7.1; Perform, in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice, such other duties in respect of the Shared Assets as may be specified by the Owners’ Committee and agreed to by the Facilities Manager; Execute such contracts and other documents as are necessary or appropriate to carry out the duties enumerated in Sections 4.2(a) through 4.2(d); Notify each Owner of (i) the assertion of any claim for bodily injury or property damage in excess of $50,000 or greater related to the Shared Assets promptly following the Facilities Manager’s knowledge of any such assertion and (ii) the Facilities Manager’s knowledge of the occurrence of an event likely, in the reasonable determination of the Facilities Manager, to result in the assertion of such a claim promptly following any such occurrence. If any loss, damage or impairment to the Shared Assets occurs, the Facilities Manager shall apply the proceeds of any insurance policy with respect thereto to repair, replace or restore the Shared Assets to their prior condition if and to the extent permitted or required pursuant to the provisions of this Agreement; Prepare, submit to each Owner for review and comment, and file in a timely manner any and all property tax returns required to be filed with respect to the Shared Assets; and Except as permitted by this Agreement, the Facilities Manager shall not assign, subcontract or otherwise delegate its obligations hereunder other than to an Affiliate thereof without the consent of the Owners’ Committee. Limitations on Facilities Manager’s Rights. Notwithstanding Section 4.2 above, the Facilities Manager shall not be permitted to do or take any of the following actions without the express prior written consent of all of the other Owners: Disposition of Assets. Selling, leasing, pledging, mortgaging, conveying, licensing, exchanging or otherwise transferring or disposing of any material property or assets comprising the Shared Assets except in the ordinary course of business in instances where any disposed items are being repaired or replaced. Contracts. Executing, amending, modifying, terminating or supplementing any Shared Agreement. Other Actions. Engaging in any business or taking any action on behalf of any Owner except as expressly permitted by this Agreement or as permitted with the prior written approval of the applicable Owner. Notwithstanding Section 4.2 above, the Facilities Manager shall not sell electricity or provide interconnection or transmission service, except in its capacity as an Owner with respect to its own Project, and as may be required by FERC regulations and this Agreement. Removal of Facilities Manager. The Facilities Manager may be removed (a) pursuant to Section 9.4(b), or (b) for cause by any Owner; provided that, only in the event of removal under this clause (b), each of the following conditions are satisfied: (i) the Facilities Manager has defaulted in its material obligations under this Agreement; (ii) the Owner seeking removal of the Facilities Manager for cause has provided written notice to the Facilities Manager and the other Owners of such default by the Facilities Manager hereunder, which notice shall contain a general description of the facts and circumstances giving rise to such default; and (iii) the Facilities Manager has failed to cure such default described in the notice within forty-five (45) days after delivery of such written notice; provided that, if such default is not reasonably capable of being cured within forty-five (45) days, then the Facilities Manager shall have an additional period of time, but in no event more than one hundred twenty (120) days from the delivery of such written notice to cure such default. No removal of the Facilities Manager shall be effective unless and until a successor Facilities Manager is appointed by the Owners in accordance with Section 4.1(c). Notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary contained herein, no removal of an Owner as the Facilities Manager shall affect such Owner’s rights as an Owner, and no default by an Owner as the Facilities Manager shall constitute a default by that Owner in its capacity as an Owner. Step-in Rights. If the Facilities Manager defaults in its material obligations under this Agreement or fails to perform any of its material obligations under this Agreement, in each case, after the receipt of a written notice from an Owner identifying such breach or non-performance and the expiration of the cure period provided therefor in Section 4.4, then such Owner shall have the right, but shall not be obligated, to step-in and effectuate such cure or perform on behalf of the Facilities Manager after the expiration of the relevant cure period. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein, each Owner shall additionally have a license, on behalf of the Facilities Manager and the other Owners, to enter onto the property covered by the Shared Real Property Documents or other underlying real property interests to: (i) inspect any Shared Assets constructed or maintained thereon, (ii) promptly implement, supervise, monitor, organize and undertake activities necessary to deal with emergency situations affecting the Shared Infrastructure involving risks to person or property or interfering with the normal operation of the Shared Infrastructure or the Projects, (iii) perform or install necessary repairs and/or upgrades to the Shared Infrastructure which the Facilities Manager has failed to implement or undertake following ten (10) Business Days prior written notice from such Owner to the Facilities Manager and each other Owner, and (iv) following written notice to the Facilities Manager and each other Owner, cure any breaches or defaults existing with respect to the Shared Real Property Documents, provided that such Owner complies with the safety requirements imposed by the Facilities Manager on all visitors. Any amounts expended by an Owner under this Section 4.5 shall be reimbursed by the Paying Owners in accordance with each such Paying Owners’ Proportionate Share. Access to Owners. The Facilities Manager shall permit any Owner to inspect the Shared Assets; provided that such Owner provides at least three (3) Business Days’ notice of such inspection and complies with the safety requirements imposed by the Facilities Manager on all visitors. Crowned Ridge 2 Access. In addition to the access rights under Section 4.6, Crowned Ridge 2 shall have access to the Crowned Ridge 1 Project collector system substation in connection with the inspection, maintenance, repair or replacement of any Project Controlled Assets of Crowned Ridge 2 on, in or connected with such Crowned Ridge 1 Project collector substation; provided that Crowned Ridge 2 provides at least three (3) Business Days’ notice of such inspection and complies with the safety requirements imposed by Crowned Ridge 1 for all Persons within such substation. In addition, Crowned Ridge 1 shall de-energize any portion of such Project collector system substation to the extent necessary to enable Crowned Ridge 2 to perform maintenance, repairs or replacements of the Crowned Ridge 2 Project Controlled Assets within such Project collector system substation. OWNERS’ COMMITTEE Establishment of Committee; Voting. There is hereby established an “Owners’ Committee” for the Owners to (a) take all actions which have not been expressly delegated to the Facilities Manager pursuant to Article 4, except as otherwise provided in Section 5.6, (b) take all other actions that all of the Owners may, from time to time, agree in writing that the Owners’ Committee is authorized to take in connection with the ownership (as applicable), construction, rebuilding, operation, maintenance, repair, replacement and removal of the Shared Assets, or any portion thereof, and (c) make all decisions and determinations (including the provision of consent and approval) as contemplated to be made by Owners under this Agreement. Each Owner shall have a representative on the Owners’ Committee. Each decision by the Owners’ Committee must be unanimous. Each Owner shall have the right to cast such vote with respect to any decision, approval or other action to be made by the Owners’ Committee. If an Owner is entitled to vote on the matter presented to the Owners’ Committee and is participating in a meeting of the Owners’ Committee but does not vote either in favor of or against any matter subject to a decision, approval or other action of the Owners’ Committee pursuant to this Agreement, such Owner shall be deemed to have voted against it. A matter shall be deemed approved by the Owners’ Committee only if it shall have been approved by all of the votes of the Owners regardless of whether such Owners or their representative members on the Owners’ Committee are in attendance at the meeting. Appointment of Members; Alternates. The initial number of members of the Owners’ Committee shall be two (2), representing Crowned Ridge 1 and Crowned Ridge 2. Each Owner shall be entitled to appoint one (1) member to the Owners’ Committee, which appointment shall be deemed effective upon notice to the other Owners. Any Owner (or its successors and assigns, acting collectively) may change its Owners’ Committee member(s) by giving notice of such changes to each other Owner. Any Owner (or its successors and assigns, acting collectively), by giving notice to each other Owner, may, for purposes of any decision, approval or other action to be made by the Owners’ Committee pursuant to this Agreement, appoint an alternate or alternates to serve on the Owners’ Committee in the place of, and to cast the vote of, the regular Owners’ Committee member appointed by such Owner. Meetings. The Owners’ Committee shall meet at such time and place as may be agreed upon by the members of the Owners’ Committee and the Owners’ Committee shall meet at such other times and places as may be requested by any Owners’ Committee member by notice to each other Owners’ Committee member at least ten (10) calendar days prior to such meeting. Members of the Owners’ Committee may participate in such meetings in person or by means of conference telephone calls or similar communications during which all persons participating in the meeting can hear each other. Participation in a meeting by means of conference telephone calls or similar communications shall be deemed to constitute presence in person at the meeting. No actions or decisions of the Owners’ Committee may be taken or made at any meeting without all of the members being present. Decisions by Written Action. Any decisions, approvals and other actions that may be taken at a meeting of the Owners’ Committee may be taken without a meeting if all Owners’ Committee members consent thereto in writing. The Owners’ Committee may, by the unanimous vote of the members of the Owners’ Committee, adopt procedures for review or approval of matters or for the taking of other actions concerning the Shared Assets. Major Decisions. Notwithstanding anything in this Agreement to the contrary, any decision (i) to remove from service permanently; (ii) to sell, transfer, assign or dispose of all or any part of the Shared Assets except in the ordinary course of business in instances where any disposed item is being repaired or replaced; (iii) that limits an Owner’s ability to generate or deliver energy from such Owner’s Project to the point of interconnection; or (iv) to incur or authorize the Facilities Manager to incur any indebtedness related to the Shared Assets that the Owners would be obligated to repay pursuant to this Agreement (other than a Lender’s Lien against an individual Owner’s undivided interest incurred in accordance with Section 8.1(c)) shall, in each case, require the unanimous approval of the Owners’ Committee. Emergency Actions. The Facilities Manager (or any Owner, if the Facilities Manager is unavailable or fails to act) shall have the right but not the duty to take any necessary action that such Person determines in its reasonable judgment that is required to avoid an imminent threat of loss of life or property or is required to avoid an imminent threat of interruption of service to the acting Owner of a Project; provided, however, that the Facilities Manager (or any Owner, if the Facilities Manager is unavailable or fails to act) must give notice of such action to each Owner as soon as reasonably possible. Tax Election. Each of the Owners shall, to the extent permitted by Section 761 of the Code, elect as provided in Treasury Regulation Section 1.761-2 to exclude from the provisions of Subchapter K of the Code any organization that they may otherwise comprise by virtue of this Agreement. Deadlocks. If the Owners’ Committee reaches deadlock on an issue, such that at least one of the Owners disagree with the proposed action but fall short of unanimity (a “Deadlock”), and any Party gives written notice to the other(s) that such has occurred, then the Owners will use all reasonable efforts to reach a satisfactory solution by referring the Deadlock to senior management of each of the Owners or their parent entities. In the event that a Deadlock has been declared, senior management of the Owners or their parent entities will meet as soon as possible, on no less than five (5) Business Days’ written notice, unless specifically agreed otherwise. Deadlocks Beyond Senior Management Negotiations. Such senior management shall examine any submissions by the Owners and shall, if the Deadlock cannot be resolved immediately, agree to convene for further negotiations aimed at resolving the Deadlock. In the case of technical or operational issues, should such senior management be unable to resolve the Deadlock within thirty (30) calendar days from the notice of Deadlock, any Owner may deliver a notice to the other Owners certifying that despite such Owner’s good faith efforts to resolve the Deadlock, a Deadlock persists, whereupon the matter shall be resolved by the determination of a mutually agreed, independent consultant with experience in the renewable energy industry and transmission issues (“Consultant”), and each Owner shall cooperate in facilitating a decision by the Consultant. The Owners shall bear such cost in accordance with their respective Proportionate Shares. In the case of non-technical or nonoperational issues, any Deadlock that cannot be resolved by further negotiations by such senior management pursuant to this Section 5.9 shall be determined as set forth in Article 10. COVENANTS Covenants of the Owners. The Owners hereby covenant as follows: Mechanic’s Liens. Each Owner shall not permit any mechanic’s liens arising out of its use of the Shared Assets pursuant to this Agreement or the Infrastructure Easement Agreement to exist against the Shared Assets. If an Owner wishes to contest any such lien, that Owner shall, within sixty (60) calendar days after it receives notice of the lien, provide a bond or other security to the other Owners as those other Owners may reasonably request, or remove such lien from the affected property pursuant to applicable Law. Environmental Laws. Each Owner shall comply with Environmental Laws in connection with its separate activities of its Project. Each Owner agrees to indemnify the other Owners and the Facilities Manager against such Owner’s violation of the Environmental Laws on its Project, including such violations by its agents or contractors. The foregoing indemnities shall not apply to the extent of any gross negligence or willful misconduct by the Party being indemnified, or to any acts or omissions of the Facilities Manager conducted with respect to the Shared Assets in accordance with this Agreement and approved by the Owners’ Committee. Taxes. Subject to Section 4.2(g), each Owner shall pay, when due, all real and personal property taxes and assessments, general or special, levied against its facilities and/or operations subject to such Party’s right to contest by appropriate legal proceedings the validity or applicability of any such taxes and assessments; provided that no such contest shall be permitted if it would expose the Shared Assets to a risk of loss by forfeiture or otherwise, cause any Owner to incur material liability or restrict the operations of any Owner or its Project. Compliance with Law. Each Owner shall, at its sole cost and expense, promptly comply with all applicable Laws and with all covenants, conditions and restrictions in effect regulating the use of the Shared Assets or any facilities owned by such Owner thereon until this Agreement is terminated; provided, however, that such Owner shall have the right to contest by appropriate legal proceedings and in its own name the validity or applicability of any such applicable Law; and provided further that no such contest shall be permitted if it would expose the Shared Assets to a risk of loss by forfeiture or otherwise. Conduct of Activities. Each Owner shall (i) conduct its operations and activities of its Project in accordance with all applicable Laws, Prudent Industry Practices, applicable NERC reliability standards, and the Interconnection Agreement, and (ii) to the extent necessary to avoid a material adverse effect with respect to the condition or operation of the Shared Assets or an increase in insurance premiums with respect thereto, keep its facilities in good condition and repair, in good and efficient working order and in a safe condition. Neither any Owner nor the Facilities Manager shall conduct its operations or activities, or use or permit the use of the Shared Assets or any part thereof or its facilities in any manner that will cause physical damage to the Shared Assets or any part thereof, or cause an increase in insurance premiums with respect thereto and each Owner (and the Facilities Manager, if not an Owner) shall be responsible for any such physical damage (but shall not incur any liability for any down-time resulting from any operations or activities conducted in accordance with applicable Laws, Prudent Industry Practices and otherwise in accordance with this Agreement). Each Owner shall exercise reasonable efforts to coordinate with the other Owners in the timing and duration of maintenance to the Shared Assets and the other portions of the Owners’ Projects (to the extent maintenance of such Projects would materially impair the use by the other Owners of the Shared Assets); provided however, that if the Owners cannot agree to the timing and duration of such maintenance, an Owner shall have the unilateral right (without incurring any liability) to perform such maintenance provided that such maintenance time shall not exceed sixty (60) hours (in the aggregate) in any calendar year. Confidentiality of Owner Information. Each Owner agrees to maintain the confidentiality of the Information, except that Information may be disclosed (i) to its Affiliates, managers, partners, directors, officers, employees, advisors, agents, consultants, lenders, and potential lenders, investors and purchasers to or of an Owner or any of its Affiliates (and their respective advisors, consultants and counsel); it being understood that the Persons to whom such disclosure is made will be informed of the confidential nature of such Information and, other than with respect to a ratings agency, required to keep such Information confidential pursuant to a confidentiality agreement similar in nature to this Section 6.1(f) or be under a duty to keep such Information confidential that is at least as restrictive as the confidentiality obligations set forth in this Section 6.1(f), (ii) to the extent requested by any Applicable Authority or other Governmental Authority having jurisdiction over an Owner, a Project or the Transmission Line, (iii) to the extent required by applicable Laws or regulations or by any subpoena or similar legal process, (iv) in any legal action or proceeding relating to this Agreement or the Shared Assets, or (v) to the extent such Information (1) becomes publicly available other than as a result of a breach of this Section or (2) becomes available to any Owner on a non-confidential basis from a source other than the Owner to whom such Information relates. INSURANCE Insurance for Shared Assets. Each Owner shall, at its expense, maintain a commercial general liability insurance policy insuring it and the other Owner(s) and the Facilities Manager against loss or liability caused by such Owner’s use of the Shared Assets, as applicable, and the land on which they are located, in an amount not less than $5,000,000 of combined single limit liability coverage per occurrence, accident or incident, which has a commercially reasonable deductible. Each Owner shall, at its expense, maintain a policy of casualty insurance covering the Shared Assets, as applicable, in an amount equal to the full replacement cost thereof. Each Owner may self-insure or otherwise retain the physical damage coverage for the Shared Assets. Certificates of such insurance evidencing the coverages required by this Agreement shall be provided to the other Owners upon reasonable request. Each Owner may provide any such insurance pursuant to one or more blanket insurance policies maintained by such Party or its Affiliates. TRANSFER OF INTERESTS; LIENS Restrictions on Transfer. No Owner shall sell, assign or otherwise transfer any of its ownership interest or other rights or interests in or to the Shared Assets, or in, to or under this Agreement, without (i) assigning or transferring such Shared Assets and Agreement rights and interests together to the same assignee(s), such that the Shared Assets are not separated in ownership from the rights and interests under this Agreement, (ii) obtaining any necessary approval from FERC under Section 203 of the Federal Power Act, if applicable, and (iii) obtaining the prior written consent of all other Owners, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld by any such other Owners, except that such consent shall not be required for a sale, assignment or transfer by an Owner (a “Transferring Party”) in the following circumstances: the assignee or transferee is an entity with which the Transferring Party has consolidated or into which the Transferring Party has merged or which acquires by conveyance, transfer or lease all or substantially all of the assets of such Transferring Party and such purchaser, assignee, lessee or assignee shall have agreed in writing to assume all of the future obligations of such Transferring Party under this Agreement; or the assignee or transferee owns (or will own upon the transfer) an appropriate equivalent ownership interest in the Project(s) owned by the Transferring Party which produce electricity transmitted over the Transmission Line; or a transfer in the nature of a lien, security interest or collateral assignment of an Owner’s undivided interest in the Shared Assets or an Owner’s interest in this Agreement (each a “Lender’s Lien”) as security for a debt, equity or obligation to a third party (a “Lender”), or the foreclosure (or conveyance or assignment in lieu of foreclosure) of such Lender’s Lien; provided that, in the case of foreclosure of a Lender’s Lien, the requirements of Section 8.1(b) above are also met; provided, however, that no such assignment or a foreclosure on such assignment shall subordinate or otherwise adversely affect the rights of the other Owners in and to this Agreement or the Shared Assets covered hereby. The restrictions on transfer contained in this Section 8.1 shall not apply with respect to any merger, consolidation or transfer of equity ownership in an Owner itself, or in connection with the merger, consolidation, or transfer of assets, or equity interests in any entity, in either case owned by an owner, member, shareholder, or other Person owning an equity interest (directly or indirectly) in an Owner. Surrender and Assignment. Notwithstanding Section 8.1, (i) Crowned Ridge 2 may elect to convey its undivided interest and assign its rights hereunder to the other Owners on a pro rata basis based on their Proportionate Share and (ii) any other Owner may elect to convey its undivided interests and assign its rights hereunder to another Owner or Owners on a pro rata basis based on their Proportionate Share and, in each case, to cease to have any right, title or interest in the Shared Assets; provided that: (A) the surrendering Owner executes and delivers all instruments of transfer as may be necessary or appropriate to effect (and that do effect) the conveyance of its undivided interests and assignment of its rights hereunder to, and which are reasonably satisfactory to, the remaining Owner or Owners, (B) such assignment and conveyance is accompanied by an assignment by the surrendering Owner to the remaining Owner or Owners of all its rights under this Agreement and (C) an encumbered undivided interest may only be surrendered with the written consent of each secured party that holds a security interest in such undivided interest and a release of such secured party’s security interest therein. No surrender of an Owner’s undivided interest shall relieve the surrendering Owner of any of its obligations under any agreement, unless expressly provided for in this Agreement, or agreed in a writing among the Owners. Transfer Requirements. (a) Any sale, assignment or transfer made in accordance with Section 8.1 or Section 8.2 (i) shall relieve an Owner of any past obligation under this Agreement only to the extent consented to in writing by the other Owners, and (ii) shall relieve an Owner of any future obligation under this Agreement, only to the extent assumed by the transferee in writing. Except as permitted in Section 8.1, no Owner may transfer all or part of its rights to use the Shared Assets separately from its ownership interest in the Shared Assets. Any attempted or purported sale, assignment or other transfer of any interest in the Shared Assets or this Agreement made other than in accordance with this Article 8 either voluntarily or by operation of law shall be void and of no force or effect. (b) Any sale, assignment or transfer made to a new Owner in accordance with Section 8.1 or Section 8.2 shall also comply with the conditions set forth in Section 2.4. (c) Each Owner hereby agrees to execute and deliver such instruments of conveyance, in recordable form as applicable, as the Facilities Manager deems necessary to vest ownership of such assignee’s or transferee’s undivided interests. Obligations Regarding Encumbrances. No Owner shall, directly or indirectly, create, incur or cause or permit to exist (a) any Encumbrance (including a Permitted Lien) to be levied against or attached to the interest of any other Owner and (b) any Encumbrance (other than Permitted Liens) on its undivided interest. If any such Encumbrance attaches or an Owner receives notice of any such Encumbrance, the Owner whose actual or alleged act or omission resulted in such Encumbrance shall cause such Encumbrance to be released and removed of record within fifteen (15) days of such attachment or notice, unless in the cause of clause (b) above, (y) such Owner (i) in good faith contests or disputes the validity of such Encumbrances, (ii) promptly commences legal action to remove such Encumbrance and (iii) furnishes to the other Owners a bond or other acceptable security in an amount sufficient to discharge all such contested Encumbrances and (z) during such period the lienholders’ proceedings are stayed. If an Owner creates, causes or permits to exist a Permitted Lien on its interest and there is a reasonable likelihood that such Permitted Lien will interfere with any other Owner’s interests in any material respect, then such Owner shall promptly remove such Permitted Lien. Notwithstanding the foregoing, in accordance with this Article 8, an Owner may grant a lien on or security interest in its interest with respect to such Owner’s Project and any Owner may obtain a judgment lien against any other Owner based on any such other Owner’s breach under this Agreement, or otherwise permitted at law or in equity, and not specifically prevented by this Agreement. Succession as “Owner”. Any permitted purchaser, assignee or transferee (other than an assignee of a security interest pursuant to Section 8.1 prior to foreclosure thereon) shall be considered an “Owner” and a “Party” for purposes of this Agreement. Accommodation of Lenders. Each Owner shall provide such consents to collateral assignment, certifications, representations, estoppels, information or other documents, as may be reasonably requested by any other Owner in connection with the financing of such other Owner’s Project (generally, a “Lender Consent”), provided, however, that in providing a Lender Consent, no Owner shall have any obligation to (i) modify the terms of this Agreement, (ii) provide any consent or enter into any agreement that has a material adverse effect on any of such Owner’s rights, benefits, risks, or obligations under this Agreement, (iii) transfer or release any property or property interests of such Owner, (iv) release or subordinate (or cause the release or subordination of) any Encumbrance on any property of such Owner for the benefit of any other Owner or its lender, or (v) permit any Encumbrance to be placed on property of such Owner. The Owner requiring Lender Consent shall reimburse, or shall cause its lender to reimburse, the other Owners for the direct expenses (including the fees and expenses of counsel) incurred by them in the preparation, negotiation, execution and/or delivery of such Lender Consent and any documents requested by such Owner or its lender pursuant to this Section 8.6. DEFAULT AND REMEDIES Demand for Payment or Performance. Upon failure of an Owner to perform or cause to be performed any obligation to be performed by it, pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement, the other Owners may make demand upon said Owner for such performance. Performance Defaults. If an Owner materially fails to perform or cause to be performed any material obligation to be performed by it pursuant to the terms, covenants and conditions contained in this Agreement, and such failure is not cured by such Owner within thirty (30) calendar days following the date on which such Owner receives a demand with respect to such failure made pursuant to Section 9.1, or, if it is not reasonably practicable to cure such failure within said thirty (30) calendar day period, then within a reasonable period following the date on which such Owner receives such demand provided cure is commenced within such thirty (30) calendar day period and diligently and continuously prosecuted to completion, such failure shall, upon the expiration of the applicable grace period pursuant to this Section 9.2, constitute a default by such Owner for purposes of this Agreement; provided, however, that if such obligation is timely performed under protest pursuant to this Section 9.2, a default by such Owner with respect to performance of such obligation shall not be deemed to have occurred. Notwithstanding the foregoing provisions of this Section 9.2, in the case of any default of an Owner, to the extent that such Owner has provided written notice to the non-Defaulting Owner(s) of any lenders of such defaulting Owner to whom a Lender’s Lien has been granted, the non-Defaulting Owner(s) shall provide written notice of such default to any such lenders, and such lenders shall have the right (but not the obligation) for sixty (60) days after receipt of such notice to cure such default, or, if it is not reasonably practicable to cure such failure within said sixty (60) calendar day period, then within a reasonable period not to exceed sixty (60) days following the date on which such lender receives such demand provided cure is commenced within such sixty (60) calendar day period and diligently and continuously prosecuted to completion. Disputed Defaults. If an Owner disputes a default asserted against it by demand pursuant to Section 9.1, then such Owner may perform the obligation in dispute under protest and without prejudice to any rights or remedies that such Owner may have pursuant to any of this Agreement or at law or in equity. The Owner purportedly in default shall (a) deliver such protest in writing to each Owner making demand with respect thereto, (b) specify in such protest the reasons upon which the protest is based and (c) deliver a copy of such protest by first class mail to each non-demanding Owner. If such dispute is resolved in favor of the Owner upon whom demand was made, the Owner making demand upon such Owner shall reimburse to such Owner the amount of the costs and expenses incurred by such Owner in performing any obligation under rightful protest, each such reimbursement to be made, together with interest at the Default Rate, such interest to accrue from (and including) the date such payments were made or performance accomplished under rightful protest to (but excluding) the date of such reimbursement. Remedies. In addition to all other remedies permitted by law or under this Agreement (all of which shall be cumulative), following a default by an Owner, the non-defaulting Owners and their Lenders or other interest holders shall be entitled to perform the obligations of the defaulting Owner, and the defaulting Owner shall reimburse the performing Owners for any costs and expenses incurred in rendering such performance, plus interest at the Default Rate. If (i) an insolvency proceeding has been commenced against an Owner and such proceeding continues undismissed for thirty (30) days or (ii) an Owner institutes an insolvency proceeding with respect to itself, or admits in writing its inability to pay its indebtedness generally as it becomes due or fails generally to pay its indebtedness as it becomes due, or any action is taken by an Owner for the purpose of effecting any of the foregoing or any analogous proceeding, then if that Owner is the Facilities Manager, such Owner shall automatically be removed as the Facilities Manager. Equitable Relief. The Owners agree that damages may be an inadequate remedy for a breach by the Facilities Manager or any Owner of its respective obligations under this Agreement, and that each Owner shall be entitled to seek injunctive and other equitable relief, including specific performance, against any other Owner or the Facilities Manager to prevent or eliminate any such default. Waiver Of Jury Trial; Remedies. Continuation of Obligations. Pending final resolution of any dispute, the Parties shall continue to fulfill their respective obligations hereunder. Governing Law. This Agreement shall be construed, interpreted and the rights of the Parties determined in accordance with the Laws of the State of New York without giving effect to any conflict or choice of law provision that would result in the application of another state’s Law. Nothing contained in this Agreement shall be construed to create an association, joint venture, or partnership, or impose a partnership duty, obligation or liability, among the Owners. No Owner shall have a right or power to bind any other Owner without its express consent, except as expressly otherwise provided in this Agreement. Term and Termination. The term of this Agreement shall commence as of the Effective Date and, except for terms that expressly survive the termination of this Agreement, shall terminate upon the mutual agreement of all the Owners. Except for the registrations required for each of the Parties and for each of the Projects to become a “power generation company,” no filing with or order, approval or authorization provided by an Applicable Authority is required for the consummation of the transactions contemplated by this Agreement or the performance of obligations under this Agreement. Abandonment or Decommissioning of a Project. With respect to any Owner other than Crowned Ridge 2, in addition to the obligations of such Owner set forth in Section 8.2 in the event such Owner desires to decommission and abandon its Project, and the undivided interests of such Owner are not accepted or the obligations under this Agreement of the surrendering Owner are not assumed by another Owner in writing, the surrendering Owner shall, upon notice to the other Owners of its intent to abandon its Project, be responsible for its cost allocation (as determined in accordance with the Paying Owners’ Proportionate Share as of the date notice of intent to abandon and decommission its Project is given to the other Owners) of the costs and expenses of the removal and wind-up of the Shared Assets, as applicable, and the restoration of the Shared Real Property Interests as required by the Shared Real Property Documents (collectively, the “Withdrawal Costs”). The Facilities Manager shall administer the calculation, collection, and distribution of the Withdrawal Costs, as follows (provided, however, that if the Facilities Manager is the surrendering Owner, then the non-surrendering Owner(s) shall have the rights and perform the obligations of the Facilities Manager under this Section 13.3): The Facilities Manager shall calculate the Withdrawal Costs and shall provide written notice of same to the surrendering Owner within forty-five (45) days after the Facilities Manager has received notice of Owner’s intent to abandon its Project. The surrendering Owner shall, within thirty (30) days of the receipt of the written notice of the Withdrawal Costs, pay the Withdrawal Costs to the Facilities Manager. The Withdrawal Costs shall be maintained by the Facilities Manager in a reserve account and used by the Facilities Manager for removal of the Shared Assets and the restoration of the shared premises when same becomes necessary. Upon any failure to pay the Withdrawal Costs constituting a default hereunder and without limiting any other remedies available to the other Owners hereunder or at law or equity, the applicable Owner shall automatically forfeit all of its undivided interests hereunder to the other Owners and shall immediately cease and desist from the use of the Shared Assets. The surrendering Owner further irrevocably appoints the Facilities Manager as its true and lawful attorney, with full power of substitution, for the sole use and benefit of the remaining Owners, but at the surrendering Owner’s expense, to the extent permitted by law to exercise, at any time and from time to time while the surrendering Owner’s default has occurred and is continuing, the power to sell, transfer, assign or otherwise deal in or with the undivided interests of the surrendering Owner or the proceeds thereof, as fully and effectually as if the Facilities Manager were the absolute owner thereof; provided that the Facilities Manager shall give to the surrendering Owner not less than ten (10) days prior written notice of the time and place of a sale or other intended transfer or disposition of any of such undivided interests. Distribution on Termination of This Agreement. In the event that the Owners decide to decommission all of the Projects and to proceed with the removal of the Shared Assets, the Facilities Manager shall take account of all the Owners’ joint assets covered by this Agreement, including the Shared Assets, and joint liabilities pursuant to this Agreement and shall proceed with the liquidation thereof. The assets covered by this Agreement shall be liquidated under the supervision of the Facilities Manager as promptly as is consistent with obtaining a reasonable value therefor, and the proceeds therefrom, together with any assets distributed in-kind, shall be applied and distributed as follows: To the payment of debts and liabilities of the Owners to third parties in connection with the Shared Assets, which are then due and the expenses of liquidation. To the setting up of any reserves which the Facilities Manager deems reasonably necessary for any contingent or unforeseen liabilities or obligations or debts not yet payable by the Owners in connection with the Shared Assets, including any reserves to pay costs associated with the decommissioning and removal of the Shared Assets. To the distribution by the Facilities Manager to Paying Owners based on the Paying Owners’ Proportionate Share. Uncontrollable Forces. No Owner shall be considered to be in default under this Agreement or in breach of this Agreement on account of any failure in the performance of any of its obligations under this Agreement, other than obligations of such Owner to make any payments that are due and owing pursuant to this Agreement, if failure of such performance is due to the occurrence of a Force Majeure Event. Any Owner or Facilities Manager rendered unable to fulfill any obligation under this Agreement by reason of a Force Majeure Event shall give notice of such Force Majeure Event promptly to each of the Owners and shall exercise due diligence to remove such inability and thereafter resume performance with all reasonable dispatch. The Parties hereby agree that all of the covenants, consents and agreements contained in this Agreement touch and concern the Shared Real Property Interests and are expressly intended to, and shall, to the extent allowed by law, be covenants running with the land and shall be binding and a burden upon each Owner’s present or future estate in the Shared Real Property Interests, and upon each of the Parties hereto from time to time, their respective successors and assigns as holders of an estate or interest in such real estate (including any Lender or other Person acquiring title from any such Person upon foreclosure or by deed in lieu of foreclosure), and shall benefit the Parties hereto from time to time and their respective successors and assigns. Upon the request of an Owner or the Facilities Manager, any other Owner, upon not less than ten (10) Business Days’ notice, shall, if true, provide a certificate stating that (i) this Agreement is in full force and effect and has not been modified or amended (or if modified or amended, stating so), and (ii) to the actual knowledge of the certifying Owner, there are no defaults under this Agreement and no events that, with notice or the passage of time or both, could become a default (or if there are defaults, describing them in reasonable detail). The requesting Owner, and any purchaser, investor or Lender with respect to such Owner’s portion of the Shared Assets, shall be entitled to rely on the truthfulness of the statements made by the certifying Owner in such certificate. Partition Waiver. The Owners agree that the Shared Assets are not suitable for partition. Accordingly, each Owner irrevocably waives any and all rights that it may have under applicable Law to maintain any action, suit or claim for partition of all or any part of the Shared Assets. In the event that any Owner is an entity that distributes its interest in the Shared Assets and this Agreement to its members, shareholders, partners or owners voluntarily, in the course of dissolution or by operation of law, such distribution shall comply with all requirements of Article 8 of this Agreement, the distributees shall become Owners under this Agreement and each distributee shall be bound by the terms of this Agreement, including the waiver of any partition rights. Amendments. This Agreement and the consents and other rights created by it shall not be modified or amended except in a writing signed by the Parties; provided however, that any Owner requesting an amendment or modification pursuant to this Section 13.9 that requires, or results in, a filing with, or notification of, any Applicable Authority shall as promptly as practicable notify the other Owners and shall cooperate with the other Owners as reasonably necessary, in each case so that the other Owners will be able to comply with any applicable regulations of the Applicable Authorities, including the filing of certificates of concurrence and tariff records. For purposes of clarification, transfers or assignments otherwise permitted hereunder shall not be deemed amendments to this Agreement. Further Assurances. The Parties agree to cooperate in executing any additional agreements or amendments reasonably requested by the Parties to implement this Agreement so long as they do not adversely affect the rights of the other Parties or violate the terms and spirit of this Agreement. Condemnation. If all or part of the Shared Assets is proposed to be taken as the result of any action or proceeding in eminent domain, or is proposed to be transferred in lieu of condemnation to any Governmental Authority entitled to exercise the power of eminent domain (collectively, a “Taking”), the Facilities Manager or any other Owner receiving notice shall provide the other Owners (and if not originally in receipt of the notice, the Facilities Manager) with reasonable advance notice of any impending proceeding or meeting related to such Taking and shall not in the absence of all Parties, or approval of the Owner’s Committee, settle with the Governmental Authority doing the Taking or agree on compensation for such Taking. This Agreement shall terminate as to any portion of the Shared Assets so condemned or taken (except in the case of a temporary Taking after the duration of which the Owner’s Committee desires to continue the Agreement, and the Agreement Term shall be extended, in such event, by the duration of such temporary Taking). Any award or other compensation payable as a consequence of such Taking shall be paid to Crowned Ridge 1 and Crowned Ridge 2 according to their Proportionate Share (without taking into account any new Owners admitted after the Effective Date). Partial Invalidity. Should any provision of this Agreement be held, in a final and unappealable decision by a court of competent jurisdiction, to be either invalid, void or unenforceable, the remaining provisions of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect, unimpaired by the holding. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, the Parties agree that in no event shall this Agreement continue for a term that is longer than the longest periods permitted by applicable Law. No Third Party Beneficiaries. Except with respect to the rights of Indemnified Owners and the Facilities Manager (if not an Owner) as set forth herein, and (for any Lender that has provided financing to an Owner in reliance on such provisions) the provisions of Sections 8.1(c) and 8.6, the covenants contained herein are made solely for the benefit of the Parties hereto and their respective successors and permitted assigns, and shall not be construed as benefiting any Person that is not an Owner. Entire Agreement; Multiple Counterparts. This Agreement, including the Exhibits and Schedules attached hereto (all of which are incorporated herein by this reference), contains the entire agreement between the Parties hereto in connection with any matter mentioned or contemplated herein, and all prior or contemporaneous proposals, agreements, understandings and representations, whether oral or written, are merged herein and superseded hereby. This Agreement may be executed in multiple counterparts and delivered electronically (including via fax or PDF), all of which counterparts shall together constitute one and the same Agreement.
